HEADWORD: Thoroughbred
<hw>Thor"ough*bred`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Bred from the
best blood through a long line; pure-blooded; -- said of stock, as
horses. Hence, having the characteristics of such breeding; mettlesome;
courageous; of elegant form, or the like.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A thoroughbred animal, especially a horse.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

